ایک پیاس سی ہے دل میں جانے کیا تلاش کر رہا ہوں میں 
 بے خودی کے عالم میں کیسے رقص کر رہا ہوں میں 
ہے دیوانہ ہوں پاغل ہوں مست ہوں اور کیا نظر آتا ہوں میں

snippet.textDisplay:
Over the past few weeks, I've felt exhausted with myself, my loved ones, society, and even the world. I've been questioning the concept of humanity and my purpose in this crowded world. I stopped seeking solace outside and couldn't find any peace. I felt lost and could hear my heart saying I needed a break, but I was unsure from whom or why. I was deeply confused. 

While searching for something to lift my spirit's depression, I came across this song. It reminded me of the importance of hope and not giving up. Somewhere, someday, better days are waiting. 

- a fan from Bangladesh

snippet.textDisplay:
Kaavish, I listened you for the first time and I feel really connected and overwhelmed by your lines 

"Andar teray raaz kai hain, khud se jo mil paye ga, dil se jo sun paye ga, na chor aas ki dor ko, sach tu samjh jaye ga, phr tu sambhal jaye ga." There are secrets within everyone which he/she cannot understand. Not those secrets which you want to hide, but those you don't really know by yourself. For almost 7,500 days, I woke up with fear of missing out something, a kind of regret. I didn't know why. Then I realized I was taught frequently in my childhood to pray early in the morning otherwise there would be "Manhoosiya" throughout the day. I used to be a good faith follower. Then I quit that habit and forgot that thing but it was present in my unconscious mind. I realized this feeded fear when I tried to find the "sach".  sach to samajh jaye ga.


Your vocals are deep, magical and amazing. This is the type of voice which takes you away for a while.
